{
  "stem": "26765.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And on the way to Belsen, I was sitting next to an older woman, about 70 at that time, and we got off together.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And she said to me, do you live here?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I said, no, I'm visiting the Bergen-Belsen memorial site.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And she said, oh.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "She said, what happened there was terrible, but none of us knew.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "When I went back in 1995, that was the 50th anniversary, I was asked to speak at about eight high schools in Celle, in Landkreis Celle.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And when I got to Celle and they had a memorial service at Bergen-Belsen, the man from the culture department, he asked me, do you think that people knew what was going on in Bergen-Belsen?",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I said, I'm not sure.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And he said to me, everybody knew because there were people who went into the camp to repair things, to bring potatoes, not for us, to bring the turnips that they made soup out of.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Everybody knew, especially in Celle, what went on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So I spoke to the students there, and they asked me, do you hate all Germans?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I said, no, I don't hate all Germans.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I have known a lot of Germans who've been very good, my uncle.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I would be like, the Nazis, if I hated all Germans.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I make a distinction between those murderers and criminals who killed 6 million of our people and many Germans and many homosexuals and many gypsies.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I make a distinction between those people and all Germans.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But there are many lessons to learn from the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the students in Germany also asked me, well, they ask me how I feel.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How did it feel to go back to Bergen-Belsen?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How do you feel about being a Holocaust survivor?",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
